wpt.desc: Swan Lake by Mother Wolf, Traditional Cache (1.5/1)

groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: Swan Lake
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:short_description: An easy C&D but stay for few minutes to ENJOY. You are looking for a nano.
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description:
OK so it's not really a lake but the end of the inlet from the Chester River, but it is a Swan Haven.

You may want to sit for a few minutes while you retrieve & sign the log so while you do that you can see the Beautiful Swans that seem to congregate here.

It is a boat launch here & may be a bit busy come summer. Although you can't PARK here for extended periods of time I have been assured by the City of Queenstown that it is fine to pull over from the launch right of way to stop & go sit for a bit. Take pictures, read a book etc.

Stealth will be reguired because you will be in view from several directions & the towns people do watch the comings & goings of folks so be on your toes :) ENJOY!

Proud member of the Military Association of GeoCachers

*****A BIG WAY TO GO Morningmom for the FTF*****

groundspeak:log.groundspeak:text: Found it with dawnie22 after looking for a couple minutes. Nice spot, thanks for leading us here.
